<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Mrol Vanir:
[B]Well, I had my log going while fighting in Kith last night.  The Mobs ranged from blue to red, with most being yellow and white.  

So anyway, Riposte fires about as frequently as does your dodge and parry.  Block for a monk fires off about 50% more than their dodge and riposte skills.  In that regard they have better class based evasion.

Times Parried:  31
Times Riposted: 30
Times Dodged:   30
To give an idea of the duration of combat and the time Mrol spent under attack:
Times Taunted: 374
Times Stunned:  22

Since my Riposte skill has reached the same level as Dodge and Parry the frequency of firing has been the same for all these skills.  

[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
