<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well I am getting very close to level 25 with my halfling warrior and was wondering what to expect at the that level.<P>First of all do I get a HP bonus like at level 20?  If so how much should it be about double the hps I usually get per level?<P>Also 25 is when I can train in riposite for the first time.  How exactly does this skill work?  I have heard that it gives you an extra attack but other than that the details aren't clear to me.  If it works do you also stop the mobs attack? (similar to a parry or dodge)  About how often does it work?   Can I get a double attack on a riposite?  Can I riposite with an off hand weapon?<P>Thanks for any answers guys.<P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Azreliah Erudite Soulsucker<BR><B><A HREF="http://members.xoom.com/handofevil/" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B><BR>"we're not an evil guild the name fools you"<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kameir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Yes, it is an automatic additional swing capable of doing from a miss to to a critical hit.  And it is quite a nice skill. With my LoW I was able to do close to 120 damage in a single round of battle, non critical.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Waylander</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">No hp bonus at lvl 25.  I believe they are at 20, 30, 40 and maybe 50.<P>------------------<BR>Waylander the Slayer<BR>Half-elf warrior of Cazic-Thule<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Macgregor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">funny story about riposte...<P>I was babysitting a lower lvl guildmember one day, and decided to pull some stuff for him to kill, so i ran out, pull a bunch of bear cubs, spiders, etc..  and stood there while they all tried to hit me..  Needless to say they couldn't, but i finally had to take all the weapons out of my hands because the riposte kept firing and killing the fodder i had pulled for my lowbie guildmember.. hehhehe..    ok, but it was hilarious at the time...<P>------------------<BR>Macgregor Bladestorm<BR>Steel Warrior of the 32nd Season **The Rathe**<BR>Order of Valhalla<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kupa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">In my experience... riposte is always with your primary weapon, you will NOT double attack on a riposte, riposte does stop the mobs attack (like a parry)... it's basically a parry with a free attack...<P>other thing to note... you don't have to be FACING the mob to riposte (funny to pull a cyclops and riposte while it's hitting your back)<P>I've stopped paying a lot of attention to it, but it usually happens a few times each battle.. a free coupe hundred HP of damage (more dmg if you use a big 2 hander, since delay doesn't matter! =)<BR><P>------------------<BR>Kupa FrostHeart<BR>37th Barbarian Warrior<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Sulvar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Thanks guys.  I just got 25 last night and trained it up.  Haven't seen it go off yet, but will be looking forward to it  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/biggrin.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Gartuff Little Halfling Warrior<BR>Rarguk Orge Greenblood<BR>Azreliah Erudite Soulsucker<BR><B><A HREF="http://members.xoom.com/handofevil/" TARGET=_blank>The Hand of Evil</A></B><BR>"we're not an evil guild the name fools you"<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Mrol Vanir</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well, I had my log going while fighting in Kith last night.  The Mobs ranged from blue to red, with most being yellow and white.  <P>So anyway, Riposte fires about as frequently as does your dodge and parry.  Block for a monk fires off about 50% more than their dodge and riposte skills.  In that regard they have better class based evasion.<P>Times Parried:  31<BR>Times Riposted: 30<BR>Times Dodged:   30<BR>To give an idea of the duration of combat and the time Mrol spent under attack:<BR>Times Taunted: 374<BR>Times Stunned:  22<P>Since my Riposte skill has reached the same level as Dodge and Parry the frequency of firing has been the same for all these skills.  <BR><P>------------------<BR>Mrol Vanir<BR>Hafling Juggarnaught<BR>Xenogy</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">What Kameir says is true.. when you riposte, it is just a block with a free swing added in.  The free swing can hit, miss, or be dodged/parried/riposted.  One time, a mob riposted my riposte. I riposted this again which the then mob parried.  Grrr<P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>41 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">23jordan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Is there something you have to wear or wield to get the attack when u riposte?  Mine works just like a block. Anyone know what I'm doing wrong?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kupa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">The combat message immediately above the 'you riposte' message is the result of yer riposte (asuuming you have misses turned on  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif"> )<P>It will say "you slash for 81 dmg" and then "you riposte" in red on the following line.<P>------------------<BR>Kupa FrostHeart<BR>37th Barbarian Warrior<BR>Fennin Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">PackMan97</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">ya gotta love when you get a critcal hit on a riposte =) Its only happened once to me in 10 levels with riposte...but WOW! That was cool =)<P><P>------------------<BR>-Alewuf Shinkicker of Povar<BR>Gem Chopper of the 35thRank<P>"Put on your shinkickers and kick some shin!" -me<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
